text: General Villegas Partido is the northeasternmost partido of Buenos Aires Province in Argentina. The provincial subdivision has a population of about 29,000 inhabitants in an area of , making it the fourth-largest partido in Buenos Aires Province. Its capital city is General Villegas, which is from Buenos Aires. ==Famous residents== *Manuel Puig (1932–1990), Argentine Writer ==Settlements== *General Villegas (pop. 16,270) *Piedritas, (pop. 1,822) *Emilio V.
